metadata.description:
synchrony is an explosion of color and dynamics! 
41664 circles are arranged in between structure and chaos. 
given a unique color-algorithm, possible color-variants are massive.

synchrony reminds me of the fact that everything happens simultaneously - reality is multiplex!

pressing 's' lets you save a .png file

if you like synchrony, mint a piece or two, fall in love with its chaos, spread the love!!!

metadata.description:
Witness hundreds of small geometric objects gather under one roof to create a cosmic rain!

Ever since I was a child, I have always been good with geometric objects. I used to draw objects such as cubes, cylinders and prisms on paper for hours. As if I'm getting lost in every line between those geometric objects! In this way, every detail of geometry in my daily life and in my other existing life attracts my attention.

Recently, I have been doing research on colors and color palettes, it is really impressive how thousands of color mixtures affect each other and the psychology of living things!

‚àΩ‚àΩdepending on the screen size you can get different resolutions, which brings out a different side of the project! so you can run this project on all screen sizes and get the output!‚àΩ‚àΩ

metadata.name: Cradle #194
metadata.description:
Billions of years old, ancient remains decay across our Solar System. Mere transient visitors to our star, their ephemeral presence on our worlds is embodied in their creations. In the shadow of their megalithic constructions, we wonder what they might have brought to us.

They brought life.

'r' - change resolution
's' - save PNG
'f' - render at full speed
'space' - stop/continue rendering

The image quality gradually improves over time. The rendering speed is reduced by default - press 'f' for the maximum speed.

Rendering may be GPU intensive.

metadata.name: Making Mole Hills #74
metadata.description:
Making Mole Hills is a space filling algorithm, similar to a flood fill. Rules have been structured to create mountain shapes, rather than evenly filling the canvas. Seed pixels begin to propagate themselves outwards, based initial conditions. After the space has been filled, the algorithm will pause, and then new mountain building will commence.

Features:
- Pixel Detail: Low 60%, Medium 30%, or High 10%. Controls the resolution of the grid
- Color Mode: Multi-hued 85%, Duotone 10%, or Black and White 5%. Multihued palettes change slowly over time. If you aren't happy at first, wait a few minutes and it will evolve
- Avalanche: Can be either None 80%, Falling 15%, or Rising 5%. This controls color animation separate from the pixel expansion
- Peak Type: Crowded 50%, Clustered 25%, Coupled 17.5%, or Lonely 7.5%. # of seed pixels to start with
- Organization: Tumbled 50%, Chaotic 40%, Ordered 10%. Controls the amount of randomness as the piece expands
- Color Frequency: Variegated 50%, Soft 40%, Hyper 10%

metadata.name: impressions 01 #4
metadata.description:
Patterns in patterns, created in code. Each one unique, but all part of a family. 

Traits: 

Palette - 8 different color palettes. 
Shape - The starting shape, either ellipse or square. 
XRand & YRand - The amount of rescaling randomization. 
Divisions - The X/Y resolution of the pattern. 

Created in p5.js
